{
  "stem": "9.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "During the war, when the Russians were there, things were quite calm, basically, until Hitler decided to move east.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he wanted to conquer Russia and go all the way to Moscow, which he did not accomplish.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When the German soldiers came to Russia in the middle of the winter, and the Russians brought in the soldiers from Siberia-- and the Siberian soldiers were hot.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were taking off their jackets while the Germans were freezing off their noses and their fingers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You could not compare.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was not possible for Russia to win the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they lost it right there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, as we know, later, the Russians started pushing west.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But that's history of Europe.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At one point, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We ran away from our town to a town 100 miles away, named Lvov-- L-V-O-V.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother, who happen to have been a very, very capable and self-educated person, accomplished to get for us papers that we were working people-- commoners.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That meant that they didn't pick us up and didn't take us to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Russians used to come at night, knock at the door-- the same way like the Germans did later-- give people 10 minutes to pack, and telling them, come on, let's go.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I am not even sure they were telling them where they went.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And almost all of them went to Siberia, to the freezing land.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, my brother-in-law was in Siberia.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Many people suffered tremendously, but nobody was killed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Many died for various reasons, but they died on their own natural death, the same way like my cousin survived and came back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Artek, A-R-T-E-K.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He lives in Israel now with his wife and his family.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
